## Dietary Alignment Trials

[[https://diyhpl.us/~bryan/papers2/nutrition/mesa-alignment/|PDF repository]]

### Randomized Controlled Trials (RCTs)

[[!table  data="""
URL                                         | Author (Year)                | N (Ctrl/Exp) | Subject Selection  | Duration  | Diets Compared            | Most Interesting Outcome (causal proximity to QALYs, magnitude, p-value)
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34377527/> | Wahls et al (2021)           | 77 (39/38)   | Multiple Sclerosis | 24 weeks  | Wahls vs Swank            | fatigue score: Wahls: -42%, Swank: -31% (both p<0.0001), Quality of Life score: Wahls: +27-31%, Swank: +16-22% (all p<0.05)
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32213121/> | Lee et al (2021)             | 15 (4/6/5)   | Multiple Sclerosis | 12 weeks  | Wahls vs keto vs usual    | fatigue score: Wahls: -60ish%, (p<0.02), mental Quality of Life score: Wahls: +24%, usual: -18% (both p>0.10)
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30050374/> | Irish et al (2017)           | 17 (9/8)     | Multiple Sclerosis | 3 months  | Wahls vs usual diet       | Fatigue score: Wahls: -33%, usual: +05% (p<0.05); physical Quality of Life score: Wahls: +18ish%, usual: -03% (p=0.05)
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27235022/> | Otten et al (2017)           | 32 (16/16)   | Type 2 Diabetes    | 12 weeks  | Paleo +/- HIIT/str. train | Insulin sensitivty +45% for both (p<0.001), fat mass: paleo -5.7 kg, paleo+ex -6.7 kg (both p<0.001)
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27216013/> | Fontes-Villalba et al (2016) | 13 crossover | Type 2 Diabetes    | 2x3 mo    | Paleo vs Diabetes         | Fasting leptin 31% lower on Paleovs vs. diabetes diet (p=0.023). fasting insulin 26% lower on paleo vs. diabetes diet (p=0.266)
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25828624/> | Masharani et al (2015)       | 24 (10/14)   | Type 2 Diabetes    | 14 days   | Paleo vs ADA              | Insulin sensitivity: paleo: +18% (p=0.09) American diabetes assoc. diet: +16% (p=0.1). Improvements correlated significantly to severity in Paleo (r=0.63, p=0.02) but not ADA (r=0.39, p=0.3)
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23890471/> | Jonsson et al (2013)         | 13 crossover | Type 2 Diabetes    | 2x3 mo    | Paleo vs Diabetes         | Paleo: 20% more satiating per calorie (p=0.004).
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21118562/> | Jonsson et al (2010)         | 29 (15/14)   | Type 2 Diabetes    | 12 weeks  | Paleo vs Mediterranean    | Paleo: 56% more satiating per calorie (p=0.03). Fasting leptin: -35% vs. -18% (p=0.04)
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19604407/> | Jonsson et al (2009)         | 13 crossover | Type 2 Diabetes    | 2x3 mo    | Paleo vs Diabetes         | Fasting insulin: Paleo: -46%, Med: -3% (p=0.07), OGTT glucose: -12% vs. -9% (p=0.046), OGTT insulin -17% vs -0% (p=0.13)
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17583796/> | Lindeberg et al (2007)       | 29 15/14     | Ischemic Heart     | 12 weeks  | Paleo vs Mediterranean    | OGTT glucose: paleo: -26% vs med -7% (p=0.001), OGTT insulin: -30% vs. -13% (p=0.13)
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25304296/> | Boers et al (2014)           | 32 (14/18)   | Metabolic Syndrome | 2 weeks   | Paleo vs Dutch guidelines | Metabolic syndrome score: paleo: -27% vs dutch: +7% (p=0.01), blood pressure systolic/diastolic -7%/-9% vs -4%/-3% (p=0.02/p=0.04)
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28440046/> | Blomquist et al (2017)       | 70 (35/35)   | Obese              | 24 mo     | Paleo vs Diabetes         | Android fat decreased more in PD (p=0.009 at 6mo); hs-CRP decreased (p=0.001 at 24mo).
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26786351/> | Otten et al (2016)           | 70 (25/16)   | Obese              | 24 mo     | Paleo vs Low-Fat          | Insulin resistance: Paleo: -2%, LF: +1%, diastolic blood pressure: -2% vs. +2%. (p-values not given, but claimed significance on paleo from-baseline)
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24473459/> | Mellberg et al (2014)        | 70 (35/35)   | Obese              | 24 mo     | Paleo vs NNR              | Fat mass -6.5 vs -2.6 kg at 6mo (p<0.001); TG lower in PD (p<0.001 at 6mo, p=0.004 at 24mo).
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27223304/> | Genoni et al (2016)          | 39 (17/22)   | Overweight         | 4 weeks   | Paleo vs AGHE             | Fat mass -2.14 vs -0.46 kg (p<0.01), waist circumference -3.35 vs. -1.55 cm (p<0.0.1)
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33844651/> | Fitzgerald et al (2021)      | 43 (21/22)   | General            | 8 weeks   | Diet+lifestyle vs None    | Age-associated methylation patterns decreased 3.23 years vs controls (p=0.018); TG -25% (p=0.009).
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25661189/> | Bligh et al (2015)           | 19 crossover | General            | 180 min   | Paleo meals vs WHO Ref    | GLP-1 +20% on isocaloric paleo (p=0.003) and PYY +6% (p=0.011); increased reported satiety.
"""]]

