### Single-Arm Studies

[[!table  data="""
URL                                         | Author (Year)           | N  | Subject Selection      | Duration | Intervention                | Most Interesting Outcome
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24476345/> | Bisht et al (2014)      | 20 | Multiple Sclerosis     | 12 mo    | Multimodal Wahls Protocol   | Fatigue (FSS) reduced (p<0.001); mental/physical QoL improvements.
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28394724/> | Lee et al (2017)        | 20 | Multiple Sclerosis     | 12 mo    | Multimodal Wahls Protocol   | Anxiety (BAI) p=0.001-0.02, depression (BDI) p<0.0001-0.09, cognitive function improved; diet dosage most predictive.
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/6373464/>  | O'Dea (1984)            | 10 | Type 2 Diabetes        | 7 weeks  | Traditional hunter-gatherer | Fasting glucose normalized; marked TG reduction; metabolic improvement.
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28858071/> | Konijeti et al (2017)   | 15 | Inflammatory Bowel     | 11 weeks | Autoimmune Protocol (diet)  | 73% clinical remission; CRP/calprotectin improvement.
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31275780/> | Abbot et al (2019)      | 16 | Hashimotos Thyroiditis | 10 weeks | Autoimmune Protocol (diet+) | 70% avg. symptom decrease; 29% avg. CRP decrease.
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37772528/> | Ihnatowicz et al (2023) | 28 | Hashimotos Thyroiditis | 12 weeks | Autoimmune Protocol (diet)  | Relative -78% fatigue, -87% depression, many improvements
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35811518/> | Toups et al (2022)      | 25 | Alzheimers/Dementia    | 9 mo     | Precision medicine (diet+)  | MoCA score +3 points (p<0.0001); 80% improved or stable.
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37355891/> | Sandison et al (2023)   | 34 | Alzheimers/Dementia    | 6 mo     | Individualized (diet+)      | MoCA score +3 points (p<0.001)
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37858222/> | Berntson et al (2023)   | 12 | Juv. Idio. Arthritis   | 4 weeks  | Specific Carbohydrate Diet  | Interview study; families reported perceived health benefits.
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34112181/> | Berntson et al (2021)   | 16 | Juv. Idio. Arthritis   | 4 weeks  | Specific Carbohydrate Diet  | Significant reduction in joint morning stiffness and pain.
<https://www.mdpi.com/2673-9992/18/1/10>    | McNeill et al (2023)    | 9  | Rheumatoid Arthritis   | 8 weeks  | Autoimmune Protocol (diet)  | RAPID3 -1.54 (2.53->0.99), 4/9 clinically meaningful (>1.2 reduction); fatigue 4.44->1.11, sleep 3.77->1.22, pain 3.27->1.38.
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23414424/> | Ryberg et al (2013)     | 10 | Overweight             | 5 weeks  | Paleo diet                  | Liver TG -49%, weight -4.5 kg, diastolic BP -7 mmHg.
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17522610/> | Osterdahl et al (2008)  | 14 | General                | 3 weeks  | Paleo diet                  | Weight -2.3 kg (p<0.001), SBP -3 mmHg (p=0.03), PAI-1 -72% (p=0.02).
<https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19209185/> | Frassetto et al (2009)  | 9  | General                | 10 days  | Paleo diet                  | -72% HOMA insulin resistance, -69% fasting insulin
"""]]

